Winners have emerged in the Clan quiz competition, organised by the Face of Niger Delta Cultural Pageant. Gloria Ofili an SS 3 student of Word of Faith Group of Schools, Benin City, Edo State emerged the winner of N200,000 grand prize. Miss Faith Iguodala, in a statement, said the competition, was initiated to project the rich cultures of the Niger Delta region among the younger generation in Senior Secondary Schools, and Junior Secondary Schools three. She said, “The Niger-Delta Region is blessed with rich traditions, cultures and values that the children need to know learn and understand their importance, she commended Gloria Ofili for being such an intelligent young child from the Niger Delta Region. “The competition had a large number of entries but about 150 met screening requirements after screening out about 100, it recorded over 30 students who participated in the competition from the different states representing the region. “Precious Solomon-Essien, an SS 2 student of Fulga International College, Mbiabam, Akwa-Ibom took second position, with a cash gift of N150,000, while Favour Edem an SSS 2 student from Eternal Seed Secondary School, Ikono, Akwa-Ibom State, had a tie with Justice Joseph an SS 1 student from Fulga International college, for third position and both went away with
N100,000 each.” The convener of FONDCUP, Elizabeth Era, lauded the students for their efforts in promoting the cultural heritage of the Niger-Delta region.